The paper presents an algorithm for decision making under uncertainty, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm is designed to handle multi-stage influence diagrams, which are a type of probabilistic graphical model, making it relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The algorithm also involves constructing policies incrementally, which is a common approach in control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.MA).
